title: Maumee Valley Wheelmen Club Race Series
Kids On Bikes In Central Ohio
description:
This is a 5 evening program which teaches kids to go fast safely on bikes.    Is intended for kids 6-12 years old who can ride a bike across grass without assistance.   Any bike in good working order is acceptable.  Training wheels will not work in grass.

We will mix games, drills, practice races, and discussions to teach the kids skills needed for cross and mountain bike racing.
course: The program uses the Gator Park mountain bike trail, and the grounds of Granby Elementary School
directions: Meet at the Tennis Courts between Granby Elementary and McCord Middle School

title: Findlay Flyers Training Series
description: The Findlay Flyers Training Series is a six race series that takes place in the Hancock County area.  Points will be awarded over the course of the series.
course: This event takes place on open roads.  Center-line rule will be in effect, and agricultural machinery will temporarily neutralize racing.
registration: The series is open to anyone.  Races are $12 each and if you register for more than three in the same payment additional races are only $8 each.. you could race in all 6 events for $60.  Cash and Check payment available onsite.
notes: More information at www.findlayflyers.com, facebook.com/findlaybikeracing.  Small trophy awarded for points winner.
directions: Races will take place in various locations around Findlay, Ohio.

title: Maumee Valley Wheelmen Omnium Club Championship
Westerville Bicycle Club Ride Clinic
description: The Westerville Bicycle Club (WBC) Skill Development Clinic is for members of the WBC and is designed to work on basic bike handling skills to help riders improve their ability to ride in groups and alone.
course: The clinic will take place at Bevelhymer Park, 7860 Bevelhymer Rd, New Albany, OH 43054 in the Orange Zone parking lot.  The clinic will start at 8:30 AM and run until 4:30 PM.  Riders will need to bring a working road bike, helmet and lawn chair.  Lunch, snacks and drinks will be provided.
registration:
Registration prior to July 6, 2015 will be $65.00
From July 6, 2015 until July 10, 2015 the cost to register will be $75
A limited number of spaces will be available for day-of-registration depending upon availability with a cost of $100

This clinic will be limited to the first 20 people that sign up after which registration will be closed.
notes: All riders must be members of the Westerville Bicycle Club and either have a USA Cycling License or purchase a 1 day license from USA Cycling.

title: Women's Midwest Road Race Championships

address.street: Logan Hills Community Park,  approximate address: 2582 Sandusky Street

description: To promote women in competitive cycling, Lady Gnar Shredders will host the first ever Womens Midwest Road Race Championships, hosted by women, for women. Pro and amateur women riders will come together to race on this fun and challenging course featuring long gradual climbs, fast descents and wide open flats. This is a family-friendly event that is great for spectators.
course:
Race Course: http://ridewithgps.com/routes/1051507
Race Course for Junior's Ages 9-10, 11-12, 13-14: http://ridewithgps.com/routes/7068495
registration:
Prices for pre-registration will go up $10 on 11:59pm June 12, another $5 11:59pm July 10, and day-of registration is an additional $2 (Junior's race for free except for day-of registration).
Racers who hold a USA Cycling License in the following states: OH, MI, IN, KY, IL,WI, MO, IA,PA, WV or MN are eligible for the Women's Midwest Road Race Championship Title.  If you purchase a day-of USACycling license, you are able to participate in the race but will not be eligible for Women's Midwest Road Race Championship title. 
Registration open 8:30am on race day.
Registration closes 15 minutes before the start of each race.
notes:
Women's Midwest Road Race Championship Jerseys will be awarded to first place winners in all categories.
For example: Pro/Cat1/Cat2 and Cat3 women will race for the same $2,000 purse, but there will be a Pro/Cat1/Cat2 Champion (jersey as prize) as well as a Cat3 Champion (jersey as prize) awarded. Race hard ladies!
directions:
PARKING: Logan Hills Community Park in Zanesfield, OH (near Bellefontaine). 2582 Sandusky Street,
Zanesfield, OH, 43360. ** Do NOT park in front of the Fire Station **
